remarkable (0.900) trusty; urgency=medium

  * Entire application rewritten to Python 3
  Fixed issue with accents. Now fully accepts accents and symbols.
  Markdown support greatly improved thanks to python-markdown extensions (default extra version)
  Highlighting is now possible. ==text== becomes <mark>text</mark>
  Simpler link syntax with URL auto-linking like Github Flavoured Markdown
  Exported .pdf files will have a table of contents (using the headers)
  Stikethrough is now possible. Like GFM, ~~mistake~~ becomes <del>mistake</del>
  Superscript is now enabled. The syntax is like so X^2^ + Y^2^ = Z^2^.
  Subscript is now enabled. The syntax is like so H~2~O. 
  Better new line support
  Check boxes are now implemented
  Fenced and in-line code-blocks are now possible. Just wrap the code with three 
  ticks on both sides of the code
  Additional options for _italic_, __bold__ and ___both___.
  Added a file association so the system knows that remarkable can open files when supplied arguments
  Tables are now supported using syntax similar to Github. You can even use markdown within the table!

 -- Jamie McGowan <jamiemcgowan.dev@gmail.com>  Wed, 07 Aug 2014 23:13:40 +0100

